<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-16T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="29" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851R.01/75: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-16T20:00:00-04:00">January
                                    16, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>92. For Murphy. Your 3575, December 30<note n="59" xml:id="d29fn59">Not
                                printed.</note> and No. 46, January 12. In view of General
                            Eisenhower’s and your recommendations the Department agrees that French
                            West Africa should be included under the civil affairs jurisdiction of
                            General Eisenhower’s Staff.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>